{"questionId":"26445","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A factory produces bags of sugar with a labelled weight of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math>. The weights of the bags&nbsp;are normally distributed with a mean of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math> and a standard deviation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the percentage of bags that weigh more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Do not accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26445","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.8a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the percentage of bags that weigh more than 500 g.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}